## Discord Webhook API

Discord Webhooks accept a POST request with a JSON body. The URL format is:
```
https://discord.com/api/webhooks/{webhook.id}/{webhook.token}
```

The endpoint returns `204 No Content` on success (not 200).

### Message Format

Discord uses an `embeds` array for rich messages:

```typescript
interface DiscordWebhookBody {
  content?: string;           // plain text (optional with embeds)
  username?: string;          // override bot username
  avatar_url?: string;        // override bot avatar
  embeds: DiscordEmbed[];
}

interface DiscordEmbed {
  title: string;              // e.g., "Build Failed: my-project"
  url?: string;               // clickable title link
  description?: string;       // error message
  color: number;              // decimal color value (not hex string)
  fields: DiscordField[];
  footer: { text: string };
  timestamp: string;          // ISO 8601 timestamp
}

interface DiscordField {
  name: string;
  value: string;
  inline: boolean;
}
```

**Key difference from Slack:** Discord uses decimal color values (e.g., `0xFF0000` = `16711680`), not hex strings.

---

## Implementation

```typescript
export async function sendDiscordNotification(
  webhookUrl: string,
  payload: NotificationPayload,
): Promise<void> {
  const color = getDiscordColor(payload.status);
  const title = formatTitle(payload);
  const dashboardUrl = payload.url
    ? payload.url
    : `${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_DASHBOARD_URL ?? "https://platform.yourdomain.dev"}`;

  const body = {
    username: "gBlockParty",
    embeds: [
      {
        title,
        url: dashboardUrl,
        description: payload.errorMessage ?? undefined,
        color,
        fields: [
          {
            name: "Project",
            value: payload.projectName,
            inline: true,
          },
          {
            name: "Event",
            value: payload.deploymentType,
            inline: true,
          },
          {
            name: "Status",
            value: payload.status,
            inline: true,
          },
        ],
        footer: { text: "gBlockParty" },
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
      },
    ],
  };

  const response = await fetch(webhookUrl, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
    signal: AbortSignal.timeout(10_000),
  });

  // Discord returns 204 on success, but also accepts 200
  if (!response.ok) {
    // Handle rate limiting
    if (response.status === 429) {
      const retryAfter = response.headers.get("retry-after");
      logger.warn(
        { retryAfterSeconds: retryAfter, projectName: payload.projectName },
        "Discord rate limited",
      );
      // Optionally retry after the specified delay
      if (retryAfter) {
        const delayMs = parseFloat(retryAfter) * 1000;
        await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, delayMs));
        // Retry once
        const retryResponse = await fetch(webhookUrl, {
          method: "POST",
          headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
          body: JSON.stringify(body),
          signal: AbortSignal.timeout(10_000),
        });
        if (!retryResponse.ok) {
          throw new Error(`Discord webhook failed after retry: ${retryResponse.status}`);
        }
        logger.info({ projectName: payload.projectName }, "Discord notification sent (after retry)");
        return;
      }
    }

    const responseBody = await response.text().catch(() => "unknown");
    logger.error(
      { status: response.status, body: responseBody, projectName: payload.projectName },
      "Discord notification failed",
    );
    throw new Error(`Discord webhook returned ${response.status}: ${responseBody}`);
  }

  logger.info({ projectName: payload.projectName }, "Discord notification sent");
}
```

### Discord Color Mapping

```typescript
function getDiscordColor(status: string): number {
  switch (status) {
    case "failed":
      return 0xFF0000;        // red (16711680)
    case "success":
    case "ready":
      return 0x36A64F;        // green (3581519)
    case "rollback":
      return 0xFFA500;        // orange (16753920)
    default:
      return 0x808080;        // gray (8421504)
  }
}
```

---

## Shared Helpers with Slack

The following helpers are shared between Slack and Discord implementations (defined once in the file):

- `formatTitle(payload)`: Returns the message title based on event type.
- `getStatusColor(status)`: Returns hex string (Slack) -- Discord uses a separate `getDiscordColor()` returning a number.

Consider refactoring: `formatTitle()` is reused as-is. Color functions are separate because of format differences (string vs. number).

---

## Example Discord Embed

```json
{
  "username": "gBlockParty",
  "embeds": [
    {
      "title": "Build/Deploy Failed: my-project",
      "url": "https://platform.yourdomain.dev/projects/abc/deployments/xyz",
      "description": "Command 'pnpm build' failed with exit code 1",
      "color": 16711680,
      "fields": [
        { "name": "Project", "value": "my-project", "inline": true },
        { "name": "Event", "value": "production", "inline": true },
        { "name": "Status", "value": "failed", "inline": true }
      ],
      "footer": { "text": "gBlockParty" },
      "timestamp": "2026-03-02T15:45:00.000Z"
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## Error Handling

- **HTTP 429 (Rate Limited)**: Discord returns a `retry-after` header (in seconds). Retry once after the specified delay. If the retry also fails, throw an error.
- **HTTP 400 (Bad Request)**: Usually means the embed format is invalid. Log the response body for debugging.
- **Network timeout**: 10-second timeout via `AbortSignal.timeout()`.
- **The `notify()` aggregator**: A Discord failure does not prevent Slack from sending (uses `Promise.allSettled()`).

---

## Discord Webhook Limits

| Limit | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Max embeds per message | 10 |
| Max fields per embed | 25 |
| Max title length | 256 characters |
| Max description length | 4096 characters |
| Max field name length | 256 characters |
| Max field value length | 1024 characters |
| Rate limit | 30 requests/60s per webhook |

These limits are unlikely to be hit with deployment notifications, but error messages should be truncated if they exceed the description limit.

